Sass.mode

Iâ€™m no longer maintaining this syntax mode. For a Sass mode supported for Coda 2, you can try:
- https://github.com/dw2/Sass.mode
- https://github.com/ry5n/scss.mode


Based on http://github.com/Brajeshwar/Sass.mode
--------------------------------------------------

COMPATIBILITY

Coda - http://www.panic.com/coda/
SubEthaEdit - http://www.codingmonkeys.de/subethaedit/
--------------------------------------------------

SUPPORTED EXTENSIONS

.sass

for .scss support, see http://github.com/Brajeshwar/Sass.mode
--------------------------------------------------

INSTALL

git clone (or download and copy) "Sass.mode" folder to "~/Library/Application Support/Coda/Modes"


Notes:
* Create folder(s) if needed.
* You might need to rename the folder to "Sass.mode" (downloaded from source)
* In the Alternate INSTALL, you'll need to do a "Show Package Content" on the "Coda" Application.
--------------------------------------------------

REFERENCES

More about Mode Customization: http://www.codingmonkeys.de/subethaedit/mode.html
Originally forked from http://upstruct.svn.beanstalkapp.com/sass/ (Author: Tom-Marius Olsen)
